1
00:00:22,464 --> 00:00:26,432
♪Should we forget yesterday's sorrows♪

2
00:00:26,432 --> 00:00:29,728
♪And the dazed confusion♪

3
00:00:30,976 --> 00:00:33,681
♪Should we let go of♪

4
00:00:33,681 --> 00:00:35,904
♪The stubborn madness♪

5
00:00:35,904 --> 00:00:39,072
♪And naive recklessness now♪

6
00:00:40,192 --> 00:00:43,840
♪Those years, those faces♪

7
00:00:44,992 --> 00:00:48,763
♪Those old scars we can't erase♪

8
00:00:49,824 --> 00:00:52,460
♪Tears streaming, facing the light♪

9
00:00:53,152 --> 00:00:57,594
♪Piercing the sorrow within♪

10
00:01:08,716 --> 00:01:12,736
♪The road ahead's long,
stumbling all the way♪

11
00:01:13,536 --> 00:01:18,076
♪The wounds we've borne
are medals hidden within♪

12
00:01:18,336 --> 00:01:22,391
♪Standing alone on an open plain♪

13
00:01:23,168 --> 00:01:26,851
♪We gaze at the stars♪

14
00:01:31,228 --> 00:01:34,816
=The Dream Maker=

15
00:01:35,032 --> 00:01:38,040
=Episode 40=

16
00:01:38,540 --> 00:01:39,820
Given the current situation,

17
00:01:40,380 --> 00:01:42,100
even if we have
one more construction team,

18
00:01:42,660 --> 00:01:43,660
it'll still take us

19
00:01:43,980 --> 00:01:45,820
at least four months
to demolish and rebuild.

20
00:01:46,260 --> 00:01:47,699
But we're only two months away

21
00:01:47,900 --> 00:01:48,740
from typhoon season.

22
00:01:49,219 --> 00:01:51,499
Your master has passed
this responsibility to you now.

23
00:01:53,139 --> 00:01:53,980
What do you think?

24
00:02:02,820 --> 00:02:03,620
I want to do it!

25
00:02:05,139 --> 00:02:05,620
Excellent.

26
00:02:06,100 --> 00:02:07,640
I'll go see Mr. Zhao

27
00:02:07,939 --> 00:02:09,940
and ask him to send us one more team.

28
00:02:10,540 --> 00:02:12,660
Mr. Zheng, Ms. Li just mentioned

29
00:02:12,660 --> 00:02:14,540
Mr. Zhao will send a team over.

30
00:02:14,820 --> 00:02:16,060
Our budget's already tight.

31
00:02:16,060 --> 00:02:17,060
If we hire more people,

32
00:02:17,060 --> 00:02:18,500
the budget will definitely be blown.

33
00:02:18,699 --> 00:02:20,060
Does money matter now?

34
00:02:20,540 --> 00:02:21,579
It's the fact.

35
00:02:21,739 --> 00:02:23,928
Mr. Zheng, money matters.

36
00:02:24,419 --> 00:02:26,299
Because this involves
the investment from us

37
00:02:26,739 --> 00:02:28,299
and those self-employed individuals.

38
00:02:29,820 --> 00:02:30,380
Exactly.

39
00:02:32,220 --> 00:02:35,019
Well, let's call a meeting
with the self-employed individuals.

40
00:02:35,579 --> 00:02:37,179
Explain the situation to them honestly.

41
00:02:37,980 --> 00:02:39,579
We need their support.

42
00:03:07,100 --> 00:03:08,500
Seems everyone supports demolition.

43
00:03:12,100 --> 00:03:13,459
Mr. Zheng, please forgive me.

44
00:03:14,820 --> 00:03:16,260
Ms. Li has already

45
00:03:17,019 --> 00:03:19,019
asked me to do this beforehand.

46
00:03:20,459 --> 00:03:21,340
I didn't expect

47
00:03:21,820 --> 00:03:24,739
these self-employed individuals
to be so determined.

48
00:03:25,019 --> 00:03:27,380
Good, they're commendable.

49
00:03:29,100 --> 00:03:30,380
Then let's start the vote.

50
00:03:31,739 --> 00:03:34,220
If you agree to demolish and rebuild,
please raise your hand.

51
00:03:54,220 --> 00:03:54,780
Lin.

52
00:03:56,780 --> 00:03:57,660
We will definitely win

53
00:03:59,380 --> 00:04:00,579
this tough battle.

54
00:04:43,179 --> 00:04:43,859
Okay, go.

55
00:04:44,059 --> 00:04:44,419
Okay.

56
00:04:46,660 --> 00:04:47,819
Come on, hurry up.

57
00:04:53,259 --> 00:04:53,859
What's wrong?

58
00:04:54,259 --> 00:04:55,960
(7 days left)
The Meteorological Bureau called.

59
00:04:56,472 --> 00:04:57,528
Typhoon arrived early.

60
00:04:57,528 --> 00:04:59,980
It's expected to make landfall
near Yuehai within three days.

61
00:05:01,379 --> 00:05:02,100
Three days?

62
00:05:02,739 --> 00:05:05,179
But the final closure
is still a week away.

63
00:05:05,340 --> 00:05:07,020
Is it accurate? Check with them again?

64
00:05:07,220 --> 00:05:08,819
Better hurry than sorry.

65
00:05:09,340 --> 00:05:10,499
So we only have three days.

66
00:05:10,660 --> 00:05:11,619
We don't have a week.

67
00:05:12,379 --> 00:05:14,020
Mr. Qi once said,

68
00:05:14,220 --> 00:05:15,780
if we can't complete the closure

69
00:05:15,780 --> 00:05:16,900
before typhoon hits,

70
00:05:17,340 --> 00:05:19,179
the dam is at risk of being washed away.

71
00:05:19,660 --> 00:05:20,939
So we only have three days.

72
00:05:21,299 --> 00:05:22,859
We must finish it within three days.

73
00:05:23,540 --> 00:05:24,299
It's impossible.

74
00:05:25,100 --> 00:05:26,619
We can't finish it in three days.

75
00:05:27,619 --> 00:05:28,939
I'll call the city office.

76
00:05:30,140 --> 00:05:31,379
I've spoken with Mr. Zhao.

77
00:05:31,660 --> 00:05:32,819
He could send a team over,

78
00:05:33,059 --> 00:05:35,020
but we don't have enough time.

79
00:05:35,220 --> 00:05:37,780
Mr. Zheng, even if we have
three more construction teams,

80
00:05:37,939 --> 00:05:39,100
we still couldn't finish.

81
00:05:39,259 --> 00:05:40,259
What's wrong with you?

82
00:05:40,660 --> 00:05:42,340
You're the team leader.

83
00:05:42,499 --> 00:05:44,379
Are you telling me no
before even starting?

84
00:05:44,660 --> 00:05:46,140
Mr. Zheng, I want to finish it.

85
00:05:46,259 --> 00:05:48,600
I mean the time is really limited.

86
00:05:48,600 --> 00:05:50,220
Enough talk. Can you do it or not?

87
00:05:52,179 --> 00:05:54,900
Mr. Zheng, we have
to respect the science.

88
00:05:55,220 --> 00:05:56,210
It's based on science.

89
00:05:56,210 --> 00:05:58,020
Science tells us
that we can't finish it.

90
00:05:58,739 --> 00:05:59,700
Is this what I want?

91
00:06:00,020 --> 00:06:01,208
This is decided by heaven.

92
00:06:01,580 --> 00:06:02,819
This is all we can do now.

93
00:06:03,179 --> 00:06:04,536
Man will conquer nature! Got it?

94
00:06:04,660 --> 00:06:07,140
We're racing against
the typhoon and time.

95
00:06:07,460 --> 00:06:08,540
What we can do now

96
00:06:08,939 --> 00:06:11,020
is to give it our all.

97
00:06:11,900 --> 00:06:14,020
We must win. Do you hear me?

98
00:06:30,900 --> 00:06:33,179
Yu Qingtian, tell me,

99
00:06:33,939 --> 00:06:36,499
can you do it or not?

100
00:06:45,220 --> 00:06:45,700
Yes.

101
00:06:48,140 --> 00:06:48,540
Good.

102
00:06:49,140 --> 00:06:50,980
Let's give it our all
in these three days.

103
00:06:51,299 --> 00:06:52,299
No one sleeps.

104
00:06:52,660 --> 00:06:54,379
We must go all out.

105
00:06:56,980 --> 00:06:57,499
Fight it!

106
00:06:57,859 --> 00:06:58,980
- Fight it!
- Fight it!

107
00:07:25,656 --> 00:07:28,440
(Beyond the Horizon)

108
00:07:38,259 --> 00:07:38,939
Master.

109
00:07:42,939 --> 00:07:43,619
Master.

110
00:07:46,499 --> 00:07:47,859
Master!

111
00:07:49,259 --> 00:07:50,520
Master!

112
00:07:51,032 --> 00:07:52,900
Rest assured!

113
00:07:53,460 --> 00:07:55,379
I'm here for Yuehai!

114
00:07:55,780 --> 00:07:57,700
I won't leave!

115
00:09:32,820 --> 00:09:35,499
(I don't know how many people came
in those three days.)

116
00:09:36,539 --> 00:09:37,499
(I only know)

117
00:09:37,624 --> 00:09:39,899
(every face was so familiar)

118
00:09:40,420 --> 00:09:41,379
(and amiable.)

119
00:09:42,980 --> 00:09:45,739
(They sweated under the scorching sun,
sang songs,)

120
00:09:46,659 --> 00:09:47,899
(and rushed through the mud).

121
00:09:48,460 --> 00:09:50,619
(They never retreated
in the most dangerous moments.)

122
00:09:51,779 --> 00:09:52,859
(They worked so hard)

123
00:09:53,340 --> 00:09:55,820
(and competed to see
who slept least and worked most.)

124
00:09:56,460 --> 00:09:57,580
(Thanks to them,)

125
00:09:57,940 --> 00:09:59,220
(the construction)

126
00:09:59,499 --> 00:10:02,820
(of Land Expansion Phase I Project
was completed before the typhoon came.)

127
00:10:54,379 --> 00:10:57,340
If this compound is being demolished,
what will happen to Mr. Hailuo?

128
00:10:58,820 --> 00:11:00,659
He's received sufficient compensation.

129
00:11:00,980 --> 00:11:02,340
And his job issue was resolved.

130
00:11:02,899 --> 00:11:04,659
He can continue working
as the gatekeeper

131
00:11:04,760 --> 00:11:06,100
in our new office on Dongfu Road.

132
00:11:06,100 --> 00:11:07,100
He is very happy.

133
00:11:07,340 --> 00:11:07,859
Really?

134
00:11:08,619 --> 00:11:10,300
Rest assured. Everything's arranged.

135
00:11:10,739 --> 00:11:11,340
That's good.

136
00:11:13,100 --> 00:11:14,139
Did I tell you?

137
00:11:14,220 --> 00:11:15,544
Your personal belongings

138
00:11:15,544 --> 00:11:17,464
must be stored separately

139
00:11:17,464 --> 00:11:18,779
to the files and archives, okay?

140
00:11:18,940 --> 00:11:19,980
If you mess things up...

141
00:11:19,980 --> 00:11:22,060
Moving shouldn't affect our work, right?

142
00:11:23,899 --> 00:11:25,859
And, you need to categorize everything

143
00:11:25,859 --> 00:11:27,416
and label what's inside the box.

144
00:11:27,580 --> 00:11:29,336
Any mistake will lead
to bonus deductions.

145
00:11:29,580 --> 00:11:31,019
- Got it.
- Stop nagging.

146
00:11:31,259 --> 00:11:32,139
Stop nagging.

147
00:11:32,700 --> 00:11:33,739
You are not helping here.

148
00:11:33,899 --> 00:11:35,300
What? Xie, let me tell you.

149
00:11:35,460 --> 00:11:36,659
This job is on you.

150
00:11:36,664 --> 00:11:37,539
I'm helping, right?

151
00:11:37,580 --> 00:11:38,220
Are you?

152
00:11:38,619 --> 00:11:39,420
What have you done?

153
00:11:39,539 --> 00:11:40,379
I am helping you.

154
00:11:40,420 --> 00:11:42,899
What have you done?
Your presence here is the trouble.

155
00:11:42,899 --> 00:11:43,300
Wait, I...

156
00:11:43,300 --> 00:11:46,460
No trouble if you weren't here.
Disappear! Just disappear!

157
00:11:48,820 --> 00:11:50,739
Write what's inside every box.

158
00:12:21,180 --> 00:12:21,739
Mr. Tan.

159
00:12:22,379 --> 00:12:22,859
Your letter.

160
00:12:23,580 --> 00:12:24,259
From Shanghai.

161
00:12:24,379 --> 00:12:24,980
Thank you.

162
00:13:51,180 --> 00:13:52,504
Today is

163
00:13:52,856 --> 00:13:54,700
our last meeting here.

164
00:14:10,340 --> 00:14:12,139
None of you are speaking? Then I will.

165
00:14:14,300 --> 00:14:14,859
Tan.

166
00:14:16,859 --> 00:14:17,739
Why are you leaving?

167
00:14:19,940 --> 00:14:20,659
Explain it.

168
00:14:23,060 --> 00:14:24,619
No, you...

169
00:14:24,899 --> 00:14:26,779
I'm turning 55 soon.

170
00:14:26,779 --> 00:14:29,220
I've been working for over 25 years.

171
00:14:29,300 --> 00:14:31,259
Applying for early retirement now

172
00:14:31,820 --> 00:14:34,539
is completely
within national regulations, right?

173
00:14:36,619 --> 00:14:37,100
Tan.

174
00:14:38,379 --> 00:14:40,940
Is it because you found your wife?

175
00:14:43,859 --> 00:14:45,300
That's definitely part of it.

176
00:14:46,499 --> 00:14:47,580
It's a wonderful thing.

177
00:14:48,420 --> 00:14:49,899
We're all happy for you.

178
00:14:50,420 --> 00:14:52,504
But you don't have to retire.

179
00:14:52,856 --> 00:14:53,460
Right?

180
00:14:56,659 --> 00:14:57,060
Well...

181
00:14:58,100 --> 00:14:59,499
How do I put this? I...

182
00:15:01,700 --> 00:15:03,340
Everyone knows about me and my wife.

183
00:15:03,980 --> 00:15:05,259
It's been over thirty years...

184
00:15:07,379 --> 00:15:10,379
And we finally reconnected
just the other day.

185
00:15:10,539 --> 00:15:12,499
I think she's quite right. We...

186
00:15:13,300 --> 00:15:15,220
In our first half of life,

187
00:15:16,180 --> 00:15:18,379
we had been quite tough.

188
00:15:18,379 --> 00:15:19,619
Now life's getting better.

189
00:15:20,139 --> 00:15:22,499
And she suggested... I think...

190
00:15:22,899 --> 00:15:24,499
She wants to take me around the world

191
00:15:24,580 --> 00:15:27,180
to travel and see the world.

192
00:15:28,019 --> 00:15:28,659
I don't agree.

193
00:15:28,899 --> 00:15:31,779
One day, when I'm too old to travel,

194
00:15:31,779 --> 00:15:33,499
I'd still come back here.

195
00:15:42,539 --> 00:15:44,460
As the Town Mayor,

196
00:15:45,779 --> 00:15:47,379
I have to make a demand of you.

197
00:15:47,940 --> 00:15:48,619
You cannot

198
00:15:49,859 --> 00:15:52,180
fail our trust. Keep your word.

199
00:15:52,379 --> 00:15:53,100
Okay.

200
00:15:53,139 --> 00:15:53,619
Come back.

201
00:15:53,940 --> 00:15:54,659
Right.

202
00:15:54,820 --> 00:15:55,340
Come back.

203
00:15:57,180 --> 00:15:57,779
You are...

204
00:16:04,300 --> 00:16:04,659
You...

205
00:16:05,899 --> 00:16:07,659
Why are you acting like a child?

206
00:16:08,100 --> 00:16:09,379
Alright. Pinky swear.

207
00:16:09,379 --> 00:16:11,379
- Okay.
- You can't just leave.

208
00:16:12,659 --> 00:16:13,779
No sense of discipline.

209
00:16:14,139 --> 00:16:14,820
Okay.

210
00:16:15,460 --> 00:16:16,499
Alright, stop it.

211
00:16:16,659 --> 00:16:17,980
If I didn't leave,

212
00:16:18,100 --> 00:16:19,899
you might not get to be this Town Mayor.

213
00:16:19,899 --> 00:16:20,700
You... Right?

214
00:16:21,019 --> 00:16:21,619
Nonsense!

215
00:16:22,220 --> 00:16:24,300
You got my trousers dirty, you!

216
00:16:24,820 --> 00:16:27,379
Wait, I became Town Mayor
only because you left?

217
00:16:28,659 --> 00:16:29,700
No. How can you say that?

218
00:16:29,779 --> 00:16:31,820
You stay! Let's see
who becomes Town Mayor.

219
00:16:33,379 --> 00:16:34,499
Alright, stop it.

220
00:16:35,300 --> 00:16:37,499
It's a happy day.

221
00:16:39,139 --> 00:16:41,700
Mr. Zheng is about
to become County Magistrate.

222
00:16:42,499 --> 00:16:43,809
And young people

223
00:16:43,809 --> 00:16:46,259
have all grown.

224
00:16:47,180 --> 00:16:48,619
I feel happiest for Qiuping.

225
00:16:49,180 --> 00:16:51,420
We old-timers

226
00:16:51,619 --> 00:16:53,100
have watched her grow step by step.

227
00:16:53,899 --> 00:16:56,580
Now she's Yuehai's Secretary.

228
00:16:56,700 --> 00:16:58,460
With you here as Secretary,

229
00:16:58,499 --> 00:17:00,460
Yuehai will definitely thrive.

230
00:17:00,899 --> 00:17:01,859
So you trust me?

231
00:17:04,579 --> 00:17:05,624
Ms. Li will monitor you.

232
00:17:05,624 --> 00:17:06,660
You couldn't go wrong.

233
00:17:06,980 --> 00:17:08,900
Monitor him.
Stop him from talking nonsense.

234
00:17:11,059 --> 00:17:13,900
Tan, take good care of yourself.

235
00:17:15,900 --> 00:17:16,660
I wish you well.

236
00:17:38,264 --> 00:17:43,704
(Serve the People)

237
00:18:16,099 --> 00:18:16,819
Don't want to go?

238
00:18:22,819 --> 00:18:23,819
Feeling sour inside?

239
00:18:32,940 --> 00:18:34,819
There's a kind of sour
you won't understand.

240
00:18:36,620 --> 00:18:37,460
What is it?

241
00:18:45,339 --> 00:18:46,099
Unrequited love.

242
00:18:48,819 --> 00:18:49,539
What did you say?

243
00:18:50,140 --> 00:18:51,299
I didn't say anything.

244
00:18:52,499 --> 00:18:53,980
Weird.

245
00:18:58,008 --> 00:18:59,499
(Library)

246
00:18:59,499 --> 00:19:00,019
Ms. Li.

247
00:19:01,700 --> 00:19:02,220
Ms. Li.

248
00:19:02,380 --> 00:19:03,860
I'll take this, thanks.

249
00:19:49,180 --> 00:19:49,912
Long time no see.

250
00:19:53,940 --> 00:19:55,779
Long time no see, Du Tao.

251
00:19:59,380 --> 00:20:00,299
What brings you here?

252
00:20:01,779 --> 00:20:02,940
My mom told me

253
00:20:03,620 --> 00:20:05,299
this place is getting demolished soon,

254
00:20:05,900 --> 00:20:06,900
so I wanted to come.

255
00:20:07,220 --> 00:20:08,019
Yes.

256
00:20:24,660 --> 00:20:25,339
Thank you

257
00:20:26,579 --> 00:20:28,539
for helping Tan find his wife.

258
00:20:28,856 --> 00:20:29,851
(Library)

259
00:20:30,059 --> 00:20:31,140
It took some effort,

260
00:20:31,660 --> 00:20:33,059
but I made it.

261
00:20:33,620 --> 00:20:36,140
You should've seen how overjoyed he was.

262
00:20:39,299 --> 00:20:40,299
I'm happy for you too.

263
00:20:41,339 --> 00:20:42,220
I went to see it.

264
00:20:43,779 --> 00:20:46,339
The land expansion project
is truly amazing

265
00:20:47,180 --> 00:20:47,800
and impressive.

266
00:20:49,980 --> 00:20:51,900
As a town built by farmers,

267
00:20:52,779 --> 00:20:55,140
its progress these years
has far exceeded my expectations.

268
00:20:56,579 --> 00:20:57,819
It's the power of joint effort.

269
00:20:58,860 --> 00:21:00,900
Everyone grits their teeth
and charges ahead.

270
00:21:01,579 --> 00:21:03,700
Sometimes, with strong enough faith,

271
00:21:04,259 --> 00:21:05,380
we can work miracles.

272
00:21:10,539 --> 00:21:12,099
I once hoped you'd be like me,

273
00:21:12,660 --> 00:21:14,499
able to abandon ideals
and embrace reality.

274
00:21:15,299 --> 00:21:18,259
But there are too many people
in this world who bow to reality

275
00:21:19,019 --> 00:21:21,980
and few people like you,
who defy fate and cling to ideals.

276
00:21:23,019 --> 00:21:25,460
I hope you could
keep forward on this path.

277
00:21:26,779 --> 00:21:27,259
Thank you.

278
00:21:28,420 --> 00:21:30,739
Everyone makes their own choices.

279
00:21:32,860 --> 00:21:34,499
How about you? How are you?

280
00:21:35,259 --> 00:21:35,900
Same.

281
00:21:37,299 --> 00:21:39,700
Back then, I was so ambitious
about going to Shanghai.

282
00:21:40,140 --> 00:21:41,220
But I only realized

283
00:21:41,539 --> 00:21:43,499
it was just another place to write.

284
00:21:45,539 --> 00:21:47,339
Qiuping, I...

285
00:21:48,499 --> 00:21:51,380
I want to apologize to you
for those articles I wrote

286
00:21:52,019 --> 00:21:52,779
about Yuehai.

287
00:21:54,019 --> 00:21:54,539
Sorry

288
00:21:55,700 --> 00:21:57,779
for causing you all
a lot of trouble and hurt.

289
00:21:58,380 --> 00:21:59,339
All in the past, Du Tao.

290
00:22:01,019 --> 00:22:03,779
That was just a unique story
from a unique time.

291
00:22:08,059 --> 00:22:11,059
Ms. Li, a document needs your signature.

292
00:22:12,059 --> 00:22:12,579
Okay.

293
00:22:14,739 --> 00:22:16,620
You go ahead.

294
00:22:21,700 --> 00:22:22,299
Oh, Qiuping.

295
00:22:24,940 --> 00:22:26,940
I'm not leaving this time.

296
00:22:28,180 --> 00:22:30,819
I bought a place in Yuehai,
on Xingfu Road.

297
00:22:31,460 --> 00:22:32,980
My mom wants to retire here

298
00:22:33,940 --> 00:22:36,259
and I want to come back too.

299
00:22:40,140 --> 00:22:41,220
Yuehai welcomes you.

300
00:22:45,980 --> 00:22:46,420
Ms. Li.

301
00:22:49,660 --> 00:22:51,140
This document needs your signature.

302
00:22:56,180 --> 00:22:58,539
How's it? All packed?

303
00:22:59,980 --> 00:23:00,739
Almost done.

304
00:23:02,460 --> 00:23:03,259
But...

305
00:23:03,579 --> 00:23:06,460
Mr. Zheng has been standing
outside Mr. Lin's dorm for a long time.

306
00:23:11,220 --> 00:23:11,819
I'll go check.

307
00:23:29,099 --> 00:23:29,860
Mr. Zheng.

308
00:23:34,779 --> 00:23:36,019
How long has Lin been gone?

309
00:23:38,059 --> 00:23:40,220
It feels like he never left.

310
00:23:51,384 --> 00:23:53,048
(Three months)

311
00:24:01,752 --> 00:24:02,620
(Six-month construction period)

312
00:24:02,620 --> 00:24:03,860
Lin always supported

313
00:24:03,980 --> 00:24:05,860
your wildest ideas.

314
00:24:06,739 --> 00:24:08,339
He'd always say no at first,

315
00:24:09,499 --> 00:24:10,819
then give it his all.

316
00:24:57,976 --> 00:24:59,992
(Outstanding Worker Award)

317
00:26:17,140 --> 00:26:17,779
Let me tell you.

318
00:26:18,140 --> 00:26:20,660
Seeing from the back,
your hair's all white now.

319
00:26:20,860 --> 00:26:21,539
- It's all white.
- Get lost!

320
00:26:24,700 --> 00:26:25,259
Mr. Tan.

321
00:26:26,460 --> 00:26:27,259
Over here.

322
00:26:27,700 --> 00:26:28,460
Mr. Tan.

323
00:26:30,339 --> 00:26:32,140
Xiaohai, what are you up to?

324
00:26:32,420 --> 00:26:34,140
Mr. Zheng. He's not here yet.

325
00:26:37,180 --> 00:26:37,779
Coming!

326
00:26:37,860 --> 00:26:38,700
Mr. Zheng!

327
00:26:39,140 --> 00:26:39,700
He's coming.

328
00:26:39,736 --> 00:26:40,220
Mr. Zheng.

329
00:26:42,180 --> 00:26:42,819
Sit up front.

330
00:26:45,660 --> 00:26:46,339
Mr. Zheng.

331
00:26:54,180 --> 00:26:54,779
I'll go up.

332
00:27:01,739 --> 00:27:02,539
It's starting.

333
00:27:02,579 --> 00:27:02,900
Here.

334
00:27:03,180 --> 00:27:03,579
Good!

335
00:27:04,140 --> 00:27:04,700
Good!

336
00:27:06,180 --> 00:27:06,900
Is he singing now?

337
00:27:11,420 --> 00:27:12,059
Today,

338
00:27:13,019 --> 00:27:14,900
what I want to show everyone

339
00:27:16,620 --> 00:27:17,579
is Yuehai's

340
00:27:19,099 --> 00:27:19,980
very own movie.

341
00:27:21,220 --> 00:27:22,180
Our own movie?

342
00:27:22,339 --> 00:27:22,739
What?

343
00:27:28,860 --> 00:27:29,700
When was this filmed?

344
00:27:39,832 --> 00:27:42,872
(Photos taken by Lin Dongfu)

345
00:27:52,600 --> 00:27:55,288
(Ten Years of Yuehai)

346
00:28:01,496 --> 00:28:04,760
♪You're but a fleeting spark♪

347
00:28:06,232 --> 00:28:08,180
